QuestionAnswer <p>Consider the following</p> <pre><code>{'abcd' 'ef'}
</code></pre> <ol> <li> <p>What size cell array would the following return?</p> </li> <li> <p>What is found inside each cell of the  cell array?</p> </li> <li> <p>What are the dimensions of each of those contents?</p> </li> </ol> result<pre><code>ans =
      1×2 cell array
      {'abcd'}    {'ef'}
</code></pre> <ol> <li> <p>What size cell array would the following return? <code>A 1X2 cell array: One row, two columns</code></p> </li> <li> <p>What is found inside each cell of the array <code>character arrays</code></p> </li> <li> <p>What are the dimensions of those contents? <code>1x4 character array</code> and a <code>1x2 character array</code></p> </li> </ol>

Question 1Answer 1Question 2Answer 2 <p>Show the syntax to index the last three elements in <code>ca</code> to get back a smaller cell array. What do you get?</p> <pre><code>ca(4:end)
</code></pre> <p>result<pre><code>ans =

3×1 cell array

  {[      1 0]}
  {2×2 logical}
  {0×0 double }
</code></pre> You get a 3X1 cell array with the last three cells. </p> <p>Show the syntax to index out the contents from cell 3. What do you get?</p> <pre><code>ca{3}
</code></pre> <p>result<pre><code>ans =

 2     3
</code></pre> You get a 2X1 numeric vector . </p>
